## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd ai-job-agent
```

### 2. Create virtual environment

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate  # Windows
source .venv/bin/activate  # Mac/Linux
```

### 3. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Add environment variables

Create a `.env` file:

```
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key
```

---

## ▶️ Run the Application

```bash
uvicorn api.main:app --reload
```

API will be available at:

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

---

## 📬 API Usage

### Endpoint

```
POST /analyze
```

### Request (multipart/form-data)

* `resume` → PDF file
* `job_description` → Text

### Example (cURL)

```bash
curl -X POST "http://127.0.0.1:8000/analyze" \
  -F "resume=@resume.pdf" \
  -F "job_description=Your job description here"
```

### Response

```json
{
  "ats_score": 78,
  "analysis": "...AI generated insights..."
}
```

---

## 🧠 LLM Configuration

Using Groq model:

```python
LLM(
    model="groq/llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
    api_key=os.getenv("GROQ_API_KEY"),
    temperature=0.3,
    max_tokens=500
)
```

---

## ⚠️ Known Limitations

* Rate limits on free Groq tier (TPM constraints)
* Large resumes may cause token overflow
* Multiple agents increase API usage

---

## 💡 Optimizations (Recommended)

* Trim resume & job description input
* Reduce number of agents if hitting limits
* Add retry logic for rate limit handling
* Use single-agent architecture for production

---

